Class DimXCompiler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.AbstractParseTreeVisitor<T>
      • GeneralBaseVisitor<org.stringtemplate.v4.ST>
        • DimXCompiler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GeneralVisitor<org.stringtemplate.v4.ST>, org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeVisitor<org.stringtemplate.v4.ST>
    public class DimXCompiler
extends GeneralBaseVisitor<org.stringtemplate.v4.ST>
    This class is responsible for generate the code in the defined output language. It extends the GeneralBaseVisitor class, so it uses the software pattern visitor. It uses a string template file, in order to convert our languange statements in valid statements to the output language.
